Name: accordion
Description: Accordion: Expand or compress the bellows while pressing on keys to hear Amelie Poulain music. (france musical-instrument)

Name: ace
Description: Ace: Despite being situated at the beginning of the suit, it can defeat the king in a card game most of the time. (board symbol toy)

Name: achievement
Description: Achievement: A medal of honor for bravery or first place during a competition. (rank)

Name: achilles-heel
Description: Achilles heel: This kind of non obvious weak point can turn into a crucial vulnerability when discovered. At least it's not an arrow in the knee! (arrow boot greek-roman)

Name: acid-blob
Description: Acid blob: Corrosive contact with the skin that leaves deep burning wounds and possible scars. (chemical liquid)

Name: acid-tube
Description: Acid tube: A dangerous liquid preciously kept away from kids. (chemical)

Name: acid
Description: Acid: Corrosive material bubbling in the air. (chemical liquid)

Name: acorn
Description: Acorn: A precious collectible for squirrels who live in a oak. During autumn, these nuts cover the floor of forests. (plant wood)

Name: acoustic-megaphone
Description: Acoustic megaphone: Simple way to scream loudly to a crowd during a strike to give it instructions or orders. (cinema electronic sound)

Name: acrobatic
Description: Acrobatic: Quick agile moves in the air, harmoniously jumping from ropes, cables or small platforms. (action body ninja)

Name: aerial-signal
Description: Aerial Signal: Network reception through WIFI or BlueTooth. (electronic gui symbol)

Name: aerodynamic-harpoon
Description: Aerodynamic harpoon: A arrow head with move stripes. (arrow)

Name: aerosol
Description: Aerosol: A spray to tag walls and paint graphic creation in abandoned parts of cities. (chemical smoke)

Name: africa
Description: Africa: This continent is considered the crib of mankind. The north part is covered by the Sahara desert. Below, the savanna is home of many species like lions, giraffes and elephants. (map)

Name: afterburn
Description: Afterburn: A turbo propulsion to travel at high speed, breaking the wall of sound. (machine science-fiction sky vehicle)

Name: agave
Description: Agave: This dry plant growing in the desert is used to produce Tequila. It is a cactus? Try to touch it to be sure! (mexico plant)

Name: ages
Description: Ages: An adult and a child side by side. One person is old and wise, the other one is young and quick. (board body)

Name: air-balloon
Description: Air balloon: Hot and slow balloon to travel in the clouds and go around the world in less than 80 days. (sky steampunk vehicle)

Name: air-force
Description: Air force: Aviators mark on their planes and jackets, with stripes in the background. (shield symbol)

Name: air-man
Description: Air man: One of the bosses of Megaman 2 with a propeller on its torso. (head robot)

Name: air-zigzag
Description: Air zigzag: Not in a straight fashion. (blood claw spike)

Name: airplane-arrival
Description: Airplane arrival: After a long flight, this plane is finally landing on the airport and the passenger will go through the customs. (sky vehicle)

Name: airplane-departure
Description: Airplane departure: Take off to reach the clouds and start a journey. (sky vehicle)

Name: airplane
Description: Airplane: A small aircraft for 1 or 2 pilots. (sky vehicle)

Name: airtight-hatch
Description: Airtight hatch: This pressurized environment rely on a thick automated seal to protect the inside from the void. (building door lock science-fiction)

Name: ak47
Description: AK47: Avtomat Kalachnikova, 1947 model. Russian weapon. (gun)

Name: ak47u
Description: AK47u: Avtomat Kalachnikova, 1947 model. Shorter version. (gun)

Name: akhet
Description: Akhet: A hieroglyph representing the sun rising over a mountain, like a disc in balance inside a groove. (egypt symbol)

Name: alarm-clock
Description: Alarm clock: Produces a strident ring to wake you up in the morning. If the hands are not phosphorescent, it's impossible to tell the time in dark room at night. (household sound time)

Name: algae
Description: Algae: Aquatic plants living on rocks at the bottom of the ocean. It's often a shelter for fish and can even be turned into an edible salad. (plant sea)

Name: algeria
Description: Algeria: Country located north of Africa, on the south bank of the Mediterannean sea. (map)

Name: alien-bug
Description: Alien bug: An insectoid alien living in swarm colony and multiplying at big scale in no time. Not sure that it produces edible space honey. (claw creature science-fiction space)

Name: alien-egg
Description: Alien egg: A monstrous baby about to emerge from its viscous incubation cocoon and start hunting. (creature egg science-fiction space tentacle)

Name: alien-fire
Description: Alien Fire: A spectral entity coming from another planet. (fire)

Name: alien-skull
Description: Alien skull: A dead cranium with long and sharp fangs. Truth is elsewhere, on another planet. (skull space)

Name: alien-stare
Description: Alien stare: Encounter of the third type when you face this monster from a distant planet of the outerspace. (head science-fiction space)

Name: all-for-one
Description: All for one: "All for one, one for all", a musketeers apology praising team work to defeat foes. (blade weapon)

Name: all-seeing-eye
Description: All seeing eye: The Eye of providence casting rays. God is watching you, even from dollar bills, privacy is gone forever. (eye symbol)

Name: allied-star
Description: Allied star: Symbol of allied troops during WW2 (star symbol world-wars)

Name: alligator-clip
Description: Alligator clip: A sharp plier head to clip wires and remove extraneous plastic. (mouth spike)

Name: almond
Description: Almond: A dry nut used to make milk, cake and biscuits like nougat or macarons. (food fruit)

Name: amber-mosquito
Description: Amber mosquito: A disturbing blood sucker from Jurassic trapped in stone. It contains previous DNA necessary to bring back to life extinct species like dinosaurs. (insect mineral)

Name: ambulance
Description: Ambulance: An emergency transportation to carry injured people to the nearest hospital in a hurry. (life vehicle)

Name: american-football-ball
Description: American football ball: Give it to the quarterback to score. The rugby ball is quite similar, looking like a long egg. (australia ball sport)

Name: american-football-helmet
Description: American football helmet: To protect the quaterback's head when the ball is dropping. (hat sport)

Name: american-football-player
Description: American football player: A light armor is necessary to run across the field as a quarterback. (armor sport)

Name: american-shield
Description: American shield: Made from Vibranium, the Captain's shield is virtually indestructible and usually comes back like a Frisbee. (shield star)

Name: amethyst
Description: Amethyst: A purple quartz protecting from drunkenness. (jewellery mineral)

Name: ammo-box
Description: Ammo box: Bullets container to reload an empty gun. (container weapon)

Name: ammonite-fossil
Description: Ammonite fossil: A petrified marine creature trapped in the ocean floor. One of the first complex living organism. (animal sea shell stone)

Name: ammonite
Description: Ammonite: A very old marine specie of mollusk which used to live in the ocean during ancient times.Nowadays it's mostly encountered as a fossil. (animal sea shell)

Name: amphora
Description: Amphora: A Roman vase to hold wine or other precious liquids during banquets. Many fragments of amphora are found in archaeological site. (bottle greek-roman kitchenware liquid)

Name: ample-dress
Description: Ample dress: A large skirt that may be worn during a wedding or a ceremony. (clothing)

Name: amplitude
Description: Amplitude: A sinusoidal wave signal recorded on a oscilloscope. Judging from the shape, it could be a sound with decay at the end. (machine sound)

Name: amputation
Description: Amputation: A hand quick removal during surgery or combat. The stump can fester if not properly sterilized. (action hand trap)

Name: anarchy
Description: Anarchy: A political movement against establishment where decisions follow the will of the people. (symbol)

Name: anatomy
Description: Anatomy: Vital organs inside a human organism to help surgeons. (anatomy body)

Name: anchor
Description: Anchor: The favorite tattoo of sailors on their arms. This huge hook of metal is attached to the floor of the sea to keep boats in stationary position. (boat liquid pirate sea)

Name: ancient-columns
Description: Ancient columns: 3 broken columns belonging to an old temple in ruins. (building greek-roman)

Name: ancient-ruins
Description: Ancient ruins: An old temple falling apart with broken columns and rusty parts. (building greek-roman stone)

Name: ancient-screw
Description: Ancient screw: This bolt belongs to the carapace to old guardian robots. (machine zelda)

Name: ancient-sword
Description: Ancient sword: This old sword is stuck in a stone and covered with moss. (blade)

Name: android-mask
Description: Android mask: A robot face with sharp edges. (mask robot science-fiction)

Name: andromeda-chain
Description: Andromeda chain: The favorite metal whip of one of the Zodiac Knights. It's composed of metal links connected together. (metal weapon)

Name: angel-outfit
Description: Angel outfit: A holy halo above the head and strong wings in the back to be disguised as a soldier of God. (wing)

Name: angel-wings
Description: Angel wings: Holy feathers to reach Paradise and fly through the clouds watching over mortals. (wing)

Name: angler-fish
Description: Angler fish: Appealing light source in the darkness of abysses. In Donkey Kong Country 2, Glimmer the Angler Fish helps Diddy and Dixie to find their way through flooded ship wrecks. (animal fish sea)

Name: angola
Description: Angola: South african country bordered by the Atlantic Ocean. The capital is Luanda. (map)

Name: angry-eyes
Description: Angry eyes: Stare with frowned eyebrows, feeling anger. (eye state)

Name: angular-spider
Description: Angular Spider: This one could fit as an emblem for a modern super hero. (animal insect)

Name: animal-hide
Description: Animal hide: Leather skin, gathered after hunting or farming. This nice fur can then be turned into a pelt. (animal stone-age)

Name: animal-skull
Description: Animal skull: Angular cheekbones and spiky teeth for this bestial cranium. (animal skull)

Name: ankh
Description: Ankh: A precious artifact that fits perfectly in Lara Croft's mansion after running after it during the 4th episode of her adventures. (cross egypt symbol)

Name: annexation
Description: Annexation: All your bases belong to us! A military invasion in an enemy country to take it under permanent control. (action arrow map world-wars)

Name: ant
Description: Ant: A small part of a coordinated crowd, living in a colony of workers serving a queen. (insect)

Name: antarctica
Description: Antarctica: The frozen continent at the South Pole is full of mysteries under the thick ice. (ice map)

Name: anteater
Description: Anteater: With its longue tongue, it can reach ants tunnels to feed. (mammal)

Name: anthem
Description: Anthem: Hymn to rally the troops under a same nation feeling. Crowds often intone this heroic melody to support their sport team. (sound)

Name: anti-aircraft-gun
Description: Anti aircraft gun: Ground artillery to protect from danger in the sky. (gun weapon)

Name: antibody
Description: Antibody: The immune system used this Y-shaped protein produced by plasma cells to neutralize pathogens like bacteria and viruses (chemical)

Name: anticlockwise-rotation
Description: Anticlockwise rotation: An arrow turning from right to left in the top quadrant. (arrow gui)

Name: ants
Description: Ants: A colony of soldiers and workers contributing to the hive. (insect)

Name: anubis
Description: Anubis: Egyptian god of mummification with a jackal head, which looks like a wolf like invincible monster. (creature death egypt)

Name: anvil-impact
Description: Anvil impact: A blacksmith smashing a hammer to beat hot steel in his forge to conceive blades. In this smithy, horseshoes can also be produced. (hammer metal tool)

Name: anvil
Description: Anvil: Everytime you need to forge a mighty sword, a skillfull blacksmith will easily transform bare metal to the right shape. (metal tool)

Name: apc
Description: APC: Armoured Personnel Carrier constructed to drive infantry to the battlefield with maximal protection. (vehicle)

Name: apollo-capsule
Description: Apollo capsule: A lunar module designed to carry astronauts back on earth. (space vehicle)

Name: apothecary
Description: Apothecary: Large bowl to prepare mixtures and medicines by combining herbs and special potions. (kitchenware life)

Name: apple-core
Description: Apple core: This apple has been eaten and only the center remains with seeds. (fruit)

Name: apple-maggot
Description: Apple maggot: This fruit is not rotten yet, but no one will ever want to take a bite at it. The apple is soiled by a cydia worm that reveals the internals and the seed. (fruit insect)

Name: apple-seeds
Description: Apple seeds: Better remove them before eating the apple if you don't want to have a tree growing in your belly. (fruit)

Name: aquarium
Description: Aquarium: A fish tank with a small bubbling goldfish swimming around endlessly. It waits for magic food falling from above. (bottle fish household)

Name: aquarius
Description: Aquarius: A goddess pouring mighty water star constellation - Zodiacal sign from January to February (symbol)

Name: aqueduct
Description: Aqueduct: Roman bridge transporting water across long distances to fill reservoirs. (bridge france greek-roman liquid)

Name: arabic-door
Description: Arabic door: The beautifully decorated entrance of an Arabic temple, with colorful mosaic tiles. (building door)

Name: arc-triomphe
Description: Arc de Triomphe: Famous monument of Paris, at the top of the Champs-Élysées on la Place de l'Étoile. (building door france)

Name: arch-bridge
Description: Arch bridge: The big pillars of this structure enhance the balance of the arch. (bridge)

Name: archaeopteryx-fossil
Description: Archaeopteryx fossil: Skeleton of a flying dinosaur in good condition. (bird bone reptile)

Name: archer
Description: Archer: Calm and concentration must be mastered to aim in the bull eyes. (arrow sport)

Name: archery-target
Description: Archery target: Aim the arrow straight to the center if you want to earn maximum points. (sport target weapon)

Name: architect-mask
Description: Architect mask: Eyes wide opened and no mouth for this disturbing alien shape head. (mask)

Name: archive-register
Description: Archive register: Writing a document with a pen to keep trace of recent events. (book)

Name: archive-research
Description: Archive research: Mysteries are hidden in these pages, a scholar exploring the library should be able to find them. (book)

Name: arcing-bolt
Description: Arcing bolt: A nice projectile curve for this ball which may finish right into the basket. (explosion)

Name: arena
Description: Arena: Fighting area. (building)

Name: aries
Description: Aries: Ram star constellation - Zodiacal sign from March to April (symbol)

Name: arm-bandage
Description: Arm bandage: An injury between the elbow and the shoulder, with straps to avoid infection. (blood body life)

Name: arm-sling
Description: Arm sling: This injury at the broken elbow needs a plaster to full recovery. (blood body life)

Name: arm
Description: Arm: Superior limb with the hand at one end and the shoulder at the other one with the biceps in between. (anatomy)

Name: armadillo-tail
Description: Armadillo tail: This heavily armoured tail could be used as a whip or a natural blade when the animal is not rolling. (animal mammal)

Name: armadillo
Description: Armadillo: This stripped animal from America has a leather armor shell and can morph into a defensive ball. (armor mammal)

Name: armor-downgrade
Description: Armor downgrade: Defense decreasing, more vulnerability to expect. (armor rank shield)

Name: armor-punch
Description: Armor punch: A metal fist in a gauntlet hitting at full speed. (armor hand)

Name: armor-upgrade
Description: Armor upgrade: Defense increasing, more protection. Immunity has been granted thanks to this power-up. (armor rank shield)

Name: armor-vest
Description: Armor vest: Protect your body from terrible wounds. (armor)

Name: armored-boomerang
Description: Armored boomerang: Try to hunt a heavy kangaroo with it to see if it goes back to you. (weapon)

Name: armored-pants
Description: Armored pants: Heavy trousers made of thick layers to protect the legs. (armor clothing)

Name: armoured-shell
Description: Armoured Shell: Some tailor take their inspiration from the nature in order to replicate the best it has to offer : here's the imitation of chestnut to get a harmful suit. (armor shell spike)

Name: arrest
Description: Arrest: A bad guy under arrest by the police who must show his empty hands and obey the orders. Or it could be a threatened hostage. (action gun police)

Name: arrow-cluster
Description: Arrow cluster: 3 arrows supporting each others. Which one will be shot by the archer? (arrow cross)

Name: arrow-cursor
Description: Arrow cursor: Guide this pointer on the screen by moving the mouse. Then click to trigger an action on the graphical interface. (arrow gui)

Name: arrow-dunk
Description: Arrow dunk: Throw an object over an obstacle. (arrow)

Name: arrow-flights
Description: Arrow flights: It's raining arrows. (arrow)

Name: arrow-scope
Description: Arrow scope: Find the right spot during a drone attack. (arrow police target)

Name: arrow-wings
Description: Arrow wings: This arrow belongs to the bow of cupidon, it has an autopilot system. (arrow wing)

Name: arrowed
Description: Arrowed: If Achille can endure lots of bow injuries without suffering (except in the heel as the legend tells us), that is not the case for the common warrior. (arrow)

Name: arrowhead
Description: Arrowhead: To aim at the right target, an arrow needs to be well balanced, with an aerodynamic shape. (arrow weapon)

Name: arrows-shield
Description: Arrows shield: A shield must be big enough to protect all vital part of the body while traversing an arrows rain. (arrow shield)

Name: arson
Description: Arson: Flames propagate through a whole city, from house to house with only water and courage to stop them. (building fire)

Name: artichoke
Description: Artichoke: An edible thistle made of a blower bud. (food fruit)

Name: artificial-hive
Description: Artificial hive: An hexagonal grid like structure looking like a bee nest. Could also be a security system that requires a special key. (lock symbol)

Name: artificial-intelligence
Description: Artificial intelligence: Smart mechanical brain thinking at the speed of light to resolve complicated equations. (head machine state)

Name: artillery-shell
Description: Artillery shell: A big bullet that creates massive holes on the battlefield when shot by a field gun. (bomb gun world-wars)

Name: ascending-block
Description: Ascending block: Big stone block being pulled along a slope to build a pyramid. No slaves involved. (block building egypt)

Name: asian-lantern
Description: Asian lantern: Warm but soft light shining from this paper box with inscriptions. (light ninja)

Name: asparagus
Description: Asparagus: A vegetable crop also called sparrow grass. (food fruit)

Name: aspergillum
Description: Aspergillum: A metal stick used by priests to sprinkle holy water during ceremonies. (tool)

Name: assassin-pocket
Description: Assassin pocket: 3 small daggers that can be easily hidden. (blade ninja)

Name: asteroid
Description: Asteroid: A big rock floating in space that should not smash anything. There's a high concentration of them between Mars and Jupiter. (space stone)

Name: astrolabe
Description: Astrolabe: Astronomical instrument to attempt to grasp the universe. (machine time)

Name: astronaut-helmet
Description: Astronaut helmet: To let cosmonauts breath in the void and protect their brain from deadly space rays. (armor hat science-fiction space)

Name: at-sea
Description: At Sea: Sailors and members of the Navy spend their lives striding the vast oceans that cover the planet. Beware of huge waves and high tides coming from the horizon. (ball liquid sea)

Name: atlas
Description: Atlas: Titan god of endurance and astronomy doomed to carry the globe on its shoulders, in an infinite torment. (body greek-roman map)

Name: atom-core
Description: Atom core: Electrons rotating around a nucleus made of protons and neutrons. (chemical)

Name: atom
Description: Atom: Neutrons, protons and electrons forming a divisible compound. (chemical)

Name: atomic-slashes
Description: Atomic slashes: Slashes gravitating like electrons around a central core. (spike)

Name: attached-shield
Description: Attached shield: When you receive a blow on the other side, you better grab it forcefully to defend your life. (hand shield)

Name: aubergine
Description: Aubergine: Purple vegetable particularly used to cook Greek moussakas. Can be called eggplant. (farm food fruit plant)

Name: audio-cassette
Description: Audio cassette: Magnetic tape from the 80s to record analog music on both faces and play it in a Walkman. (sound)

Name: aura
Description: Aura: A spectral energy field surrounding a living organism. This is slowly pulsating. (body energy rank)

Name: australia
Description: Australia: Big island or continent? It was the last huge land conquered by colonists against native aboriginal people. (australia map)

Name: auto-repair
